# Design Tokens: Color & Size System

## Core Philosophy (CRITICAL)
- Our system uses a centralized Design Token architecture driven by CSS Variables.
- UnoCSS and PrimeVue are strictly mapped to these variables.
- **NEVER** use raw hex codes, RGB values, or `rem`/`em` sizing in templates or styles.

## 🎨 Color System Anti-Patterns (FORBIDDEN)
- ❌ `class="text-[#333333]"` or `class="bg-[#F5F5F5]"` (No arbitrary UnoCSS hex colors).
- ❌ `color: #ff0000;` in `<style>` blocks.
- ❌ `class="text-red-500"`, `class="bg-blue-200"`, `class="text-gray-500"`, `class="bg-slate-100"` — ALL Tailwind built-in color palette classes are FORBIDDEN. These are static colors that do not respond to theme switching.
- ❌ `class="text-white"`, `class="text-black"`, `class="bg-white"`, `class="bg-black"` — Tailwind color aliases, equally FORBIDDEN.
- ❌ `dark:bg-gray-900`, `dark:text-white` — FORBIDDEN. Semantic tokens auto-respond to dark mode.
- ✅ **DO:** Use semantic UnoCSS classes mapped to our theme: `text-primary`, `bg-background`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border border-solid border-border`, `bg-muted`, `text-danger`, `bg-primary-light`.

## Theme Preset Source-Data Exception

Raw `#RRGGBB` values are allowed only as canonical theme source data, not as UI implementation colors.

Allowed files:
- `src/constants/theme.ts` — explicit `THEME_PRESETS` source data.
- `src/constants/theme.spec.ts` and token validation scripts — expected values and contrast checks.
- `src/utils/theme/**` — color parsing, conversion, derivation, validation, and compiler internals.

Rules for this exception:
- Preset colors MUST remain valid full HEX values (`#RRGGBB`, no alpha, no shorthand).
- `THEME_PRESETS` SHOULD use `CompleteThemePreset[]` and define both `light` and `dark` mode explicitly.
- Preset edits MUST NOT modify Theme Engine runtime modules unless the task explicitly asks for engine behavior changes.
- Every preset and mode MUST include complete semantic families: `primary`, `accent`, `success`, `warn`, `danger`, `info`, `help`, base scalar tokens, neutral tokens, and independent `sidebar` tokens.
- After changing preset data, run `pnpm exec tsx scripts/upgrade-all-themes.mjs`, `pnpm exec vitest run src/constants/theme.spec.ts src/utils/theme`, and ESLint for the touched theme files.

## 📏 Size & Spacing System Anti-Patterns (FORBIDDEN)
- ❌ `class="w-4"`, `class="p-10"`, `class="mt-2"` — Unitless numeric shorthands (defaulting to `rem`) are **ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN**.
- ❌ `class="w-[16rem]"`, `class="h-[2em]"` — `rem/em` units are **ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN**.
- ❌ `font-size: 14px;` in `<style>` blocks.
- ✅ **PERMITTED arbitrary forms for sizing**:
  - `w-[var(--spacing-2xl)]` — CSS variable wrapper.
  - Explicit units when token classes cannot express intent, with strict order: `vw/vh > % > px`.
- ✅ **DO:** Use the established scale: `p-sm`, `m-md`, `gap-lg`, `text-sm`, `rounded-md`.

> **ABSOLUTE RULE**: `rem/em` are forbidden for sizing and spacing. If a size cannot be expressed by token scale, use explicit units with priority `vw/vh > % > px`, or request token extension from the design engine (`src/design-engine/theme/index.ts`).

## Integration Enforcement
If you need a color or spacing that does not exist in the semantic token list, **STOP**. Do not hardcode it. Query the existing design engine constants or request a token extension.

