## Absorbed Blueprint Examples

### Theme & Design Tokens Blueprint (Merged)

When building UI components, strictly adhere to semantic classes mapped from central CSS variables.

- **Backgrounds:** `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `bg-muted`
- **Typography:** `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `text-primary-foreground`
- **Borders:** `border border-solid border-border`, `border border-solid border-input`, `border-b border-b-solid border-border`
- **States:** `text-primary`, `bg-success`, `text-danger`, `bg-warn`

```vue
<div class="p-md bg-card border border-solid border-border rounded-lg flex flex-col gap-sm">
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground">
    User Profile
  </h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
    Manage your account settings.
  </p>
  <Button class="px-md py-sm bg-primary text-primary-foreground rounded-md">
    Save Changes
  </Button>
</div>
```

## Border Composition Contract

Semantic border color classes are not complete drawing instructions by themselves. Any drawing border MUST include explicit style:

- Full shell: `border border-solid border-border`
- Transparent shell: `border border-solid border-transparent`
- Divider: `border-b border-b-solid border-border`
- Sidebar separator: `border-r border-r-solid border-sidebar-border`

`border` alone is forbidden in this architecture even though UnoCSS can generate CSS for it.

