## Complete Color Token Family Reference

**SSOT**: `src/utils/theme/metadata.ts` (`COLOR_FAMILIES`)

The design engine generates 62+ CSS custom properties organized in four tiers. Every UnoCSS color class (`bg-*`, `text-*`, `border-*`) maps to one of these tokens.

### Tier 1 — Single Tokens (5 tokens)

One CSS variable each. No variants.

| Token | CSS variable | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `background` | `--background` | Page canvas (`bg-background`) |
| `foreground` | `--foreground` | Primary body text (`text-foreground`) |
| `border` | `--border` | Structural dividers (`border-border`) |
| `input` | `--input` | Input field borders |
| `ring` | `--ring` | Focus rings (`focus:ring-ring`) |

### Tier 2 — Pair Families (4 families × 2 = 8 tokens)

Each family generates a DEFAULT token and a `-foreground` token:

| Family | Tokens generated | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `card` | `card`, `card-foreground` | Panel / card surfaces (`bg-card`) |
| `popover` | `popover`, `popover-foreground` | Dropdowns, tooltips |
| `secondary` | `secondary`, `secondary-foreground` | Secondary surfaces and text |
| `muted` | `muted`, `muted-foreground` | Subtle backgrounds, de-emphasized text |

Usage: `bg-card`, `text-card-foreground`, `bg-muted`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-secondary`, `text-secondary-foreground`

### Tier 3 — Quad Families (7 families × 6 = 42 tokens)

Each family generates 6 variant tokens:

| State suffix | Example (primary) | Description |
|---|---|---|
| _(none)_ | `primary` | Default background / fill |
| `-foreground` | `primary-foreground` | Text/icon on top of default fill |
| `-hover` | `primary-hover` | Hover state background |
| `-hover-foreground` | `primary-hover-foreground` | Text/icon on hover fill |
| `-light` | `primary-light` | Subtle tinted background |
| `-light-foreground` | `primary-light-foreground` | Text on light tinted background |

Families: `primary`, `accent`, `danger`, `warn`, `success`, `info`, `help`

Common usage patterns:
```html
<!-- Primary CTA button -->
<div class="bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary-hover">

<!-- Danger badge -->
<span class="bg-danger-light text-danger-light-foreground">

<!-- Focus preselection -->
<div class="bg-primary-light text-primary">

<!-- Accent tab indicator -->
<div class="bg-accent text-accent-foreground">
```

> **Rule**: Solid interactive surfaces SHOULD prefer `primary-hover` / `*-hover`. For translucent material layers, low-emphasis list hover, glass surfaces, and tokenized overlays, semantic token opacity forms such as `bg-primary/10` or `bg-foreground/[0.04]` are allowed. Arbitrary palette colors and raw non-semantic hover colors remain forbidden.

### Tier 4 — Sidebar Family (8 dedicated tokens)

Sidebar uses its own isolated token family to allow independent theming from the main content area.

| CSS variable | UnoCSS class | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `--sidebar-background` | `bg-sidebar-background` | Sidebar panel background |
| `--sidebar-foreground` | `text-sidebar-foreground` | Sidebar text and icons |
| `--sidebar-primary` | `bg-sidebar-primary` | Active/selected item background |
| `--sidebar-primary-foreground` | `text-sidebar-primary-foreground` | Text on active item |
| `--sidebar-accent` | `bg-sidebar-accent` | Hover state for sidebar items |
| `--sidebar-accent-foreground` | `text-sidebar-accent-foreground` | Text on hovered sidebar item |
| `--sidebar-border` | `border-sidebar-border` | Sidebar internal borders |
| `--sidebar-ring` | `ring-sidebar-ring` | Focus rings inside sidebar |

> **Rule**: Sidebar components MUST use `sidebar-*` tokens, NOT `primary` or `card` tokens. This ensures sidebar and content area can be themed independently.
